<strong>(FSG)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Immersive and propulsive and I never wanted it to end.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Leslie Jamison</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265138" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/karl-ove-knausgaard-niall-williams-daniyal-mueenuddin-and-more-21-new-books-out-today/attachment/231404078/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078.jpg" data-orig-size="331,500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Other Side of Change" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265138" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078-199x300.jpg" alt="The Other Side of Change" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/231404078.jpg 331w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Maya Shankar, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593713686" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Other Side of Change: Who We Become When Life Makes Other Plans</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Riverhead)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A rare combination of beautiful storytelling, cognitive science, and wholehearted wisdom.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Brené Brown</p>
